******
[1] North Kivu (Beni): outbreak awaiting official confirmation
Date: Fri 8 Oct 2021
Source: Global Public Health Intelligence Network, Emergency Management Branch /Public Health Agency of Canada, Government of Canada/ [edited]



Ebola: suspected case of Ebola in Democratic Republic of the Congo (from unconfirmed preliminary report from local sources)

Summary: A case of Ebola has been reported in the eastern Democratic Republic of Congo. The official confirmation is pending. The case is stated to be a 2 year old in a densely-populated neighbourhood of the city of Beni, one of the epicentres of the 2018-2020 outbreak. Three of the baby's neighbours presented symptoms consistent with Ebola in September 2021 and then died, however, none were tested for the virus.

Original article
----------------
GOMA, Democratic Republic of Congo (Reuters) - A case of Ebola has been confirmed in eastern Democratic Republic of Congo, according to an internal report on Fri 8 Oct 2021 from the national biomedical laboratory, 5 months after the end of the most recent outbreak there. Congo's health minister declined to confirm the information, but said a statement would be published shortly.

It was not immediately known if the case was related to the 2018-2020 outbreak that killed more than 2200 people in eastern Congo, or the flare-up that killed 6 this year [2021]. The report from the biomedical lab, the INRB, said the positive result came from a 2 year old in a densely-populated neighbourhood of the city of Beni, one of the epicentres of the 2018--2020 outbreak, which was the 2nd deadliest on record. Three of the baby's neighbours presented symptoms consistent with Ebola last month [Sep 2021] and then died, the report said, but none were tested for the virus.

It is not unusual for sporadic cases to occur following a major outbreak, health experts say. Particles of the virus can remain present in semen for months after recovery from an infection. [Disturbing observation when the case is a 2 year old. - Mod.SH]

Congo has recorded 11 outbreaks since the disease, which causes severe vomiting and diarrhoea and is spread through contact with body fluids, was discovered near its Ebola River in 1976. The country's equatorial forests have been a breeding ground for the virus.

The original source is available at: https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2021-10-08/new-ebola-case-confirmed-in-eastern-congo-lab-report.

