[The Reuters report states the etiology of Ebola is confirmed, but the GPHIN report states "unconfirmed preliminary report".

The last outbreak of Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) that was first detected 7 Feb 2021 after the laboratory confirmation of one case in Butembo, North Kivu Province was declared ended in May 2021. That outbreak was linked to the 2-year long outbreak that took place in North Kivu and Ituri provinces from 2018-2020. It is not clear whether the child in Beni reported here died, as did 3 neighbors (age?) earlier. Sequencing of the virus will indicate whether it is a new emergence event, but may be human to human transmission from a previously infected individual with persistent virus. Although we have now received official confirmation, we will watch for further information and would be grateful for reports from informed sources. - Mod.LK

